# Quality gates

Run all checks before opening a PR. CI enforces the same commands.
{% if python != 'none' %}
## Commands

```bash
{% if python == 'component' %}cd backend && {% endif %}uv sync        # install / sync dependencies

make check      # full CI suite: format-check + lint + typecheck + test with coverage
make fix        # auto-fix: ruff format + ruff check --fix (safe to run anytime)
make test       # run tests only (no coverage, faster)
make test-cov   # run tests with coverage report
make lint       # ruff check only
make typecheck  # pyright only
```

Underlying commands (run via `uv run` in the project{% if python == 'component' %}'s `backend/` directory{% endif %}):

```bash
uv run ruff format --check    # format-check
uv run ruff check             # lint
uv run pyright                # typecheck
uv run pytest --cov           # test with coverage
```

## CI mapping

| `make` target | What runs |
|---|---|
| `fmt-check` | `ruff format --check` |
| `lint` | `ruff check` |
| `typecheck` | `pyright` |
| `test-cov` | `pytest --cov --cov-report=term --cov-report=html` |
| `check` | all of the above |

CI runs `make check` on every push and pull request.

